<section class="card">
  <h1>About Damn Kitty Works</h1>
  <p>
    Damn Kitty Works is a small place for figuring out AI, robotics, 3D printing, hydroponics, and other intimidating tools in plain English.
  </p>
  <p>
    I am not trying to look like an expert. I am trying to make the confusing parts easier to see.
  </p>
  <p>
    Most of what shows up here starts as a question: Can this be simpler? Can a normal person try it? What broke? What did I misunderstand? What would make this less mysterious for the next person?
  </p>
  <p>
Posts may change over time as I learn more. When a change matters, I try to leave a note so the thinking stays visible instead of pretending the first version was perfect.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="card">
  <h2>What this site is for</h2>
  <p>
    <strong>Small experiments.</strong> Useful tests, notes, parts lists, workflows, and demos that make hard things feel more approachable.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Plain-English explanations.</strong> If something only makes sense to people already inside the club, it probably needs better instructions.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Visible mistakes.</strong> Wrong turns are part of the work. Sometimes the most useful thing is seeing what did not work and why.
  </p>
</section>

